On the International Day in Support of Victims of Torture, the United States reaffirms its opposition to all forms of inhumane treatment and its commitment to eliminating torture. The article highlights instances of torture in different countries, such as Ukraine, Russia, Syria, and North Korea. It emphasizes the destructive impact of torture on lives, families, and communities. The United States believes it is essential to hold itself to the same standards it expects from others and continues to prohibit torture in all forms. The country is also the largest contributor to the UN Voluntary Fund for Victims of Torture and provides funding for programs that support survivors of torture. The article calls on all nations to support rehabilitation and justice for torture survivors and work towards the elimination of torture.